						<summary>

						<p>North wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Bṛihadīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kulōttuṅga III year 13 = 1190 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete record commences with the <hi rend="italic">praśasti Pugaḻ vā[y*]ttu vaḷam-peruga,</hi> etc., of the king, of which only portions can be made out.</p>						

						<p>It records an order of the king issued on the 160th day of the thirteenth year of his reign. It purports to be a copy of the king's order in connection with some transaction of a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> land. Mentions the sub-division Karavaḷa-nāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
